xtc.lang

Class CPrinter

  • java.lang.Object
    • xtc.tree.Visitor
      • xtc.lang.CPrinter

  • public class CPrinter
extends Visitor
    A pretty printer for C.

    A note on operator precedence: This printer uses precedence levels to control when to print parentheses around expressions. The actual precedence values are the standard C precedence levels multiplied by ten.

    Version:
    $Revision: 1.75 $

    • Method Detail

      • containsLongType

        protected boolean containsLongType(GNode specs)
        Determine whether the specified generic node contains a long type definition. A long type definition requires multiple lines for readability. Examples include enumeration, structure, and union type definitions.
        Parameters:
        specs - The generic node, representing a list of specifiers.
        Returns:
        true if the specifiers contain a long type specifier.

      • isLongDeclaration

        protected boolean isLongDeclaration(GNode decl)
        Determine whether the specified declaration is long. A long declaration requires multiple lines for readability. Examples include declarations containing enumeration, structure, and union type definitions.
        Parameters:
        decl - The declaration.
        Returns:
        true if the specified declaration is long.

      • formatAsTruthValue

        protected void formatAsTruthValue(Node n)
        Print an expression as a truth value. This method prints the specified node. If that node represents an assignment expression and EXTRA_PARENTHESES is true, this method adds an extra set of parentheses around the expression to avoid gcc warnings.
        Parameters:
        n - The node to print.

      • startStatement

        protected boolean startStatement(int kind,
                     Node node)
        Start a new statement. This method and the corresponding prepareNested() and endStatement(boolean) methods provide a reasonable default for newlines and indentation when printing statements. They manage the isDeclaration, isStatement, isOpenLine, isNested, and isIfElse flags.
        Parameters:
        kind - The kind of statement, which must be one of the three statement flags defined by this class.
        node - The statement's node.
        Returns:
        The flag for whether the current statement is nested.

      • enterContext

        protected int enterContext(int prec)
        Enter an expression context. The new context has the specified precedence level.
        Parameters:

        Returns:
        The previous precedence level.
        See Also:
        exitContext(int)

      • enterContext

        protected int enterContext()
        Enter an expression context. The new context is appropriate for an operand opposite the associativity of the current operator. For example, when printing an additive expression, this method should be called before printing the second operand, as additive operators associate left-to-right.
        Returns:
        The previous precedence level.
        See Also:
        exitContext(int)
